My own take on a Super Heavy aerial transport for Space Marines dubbed the Storm Crane. Sized to be used in Epic/Legion Imperialis games.

Unique in its role, Storm Cranes are able to deliver a variety of assets to the front. From 10 fully embarked rhinos, or 4 kratos heavy battle tanks or any other armored detachment, Storm Cranes are able to bring full detachments of armor needed on the battle field. Protected by heavy plating and a pair of void shields this flyer can withstand any punishment short of anti-titan weapons. Ensuring its cargo successfully arrives where it is needed. Each Strom Crane is armed with two audax heavy bolter arrays and two titan sized havoc launchers making it a formidable assault craft that can break through enemy lines. A truly armored work horse, Space Marine legions relied heavily on these vehicles throughout the crusade and into the Heresy.


While I designed most of this using 3D Builder, I did borrow some choice parts from free kits.
Winglets/Audax Turrets from MKHand Industries
Thruster Turbine and Exhaust from IronMaster
Titan Hatch and Void Shields from Danny_Cyanide

This is a remix of the impressive STROGANOFF original Epic Scale Landing Craft found at https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/epic-scale-landing-craft. As I wanted to print it on FDM I modified it to have the less non-fdm printable detail removed (turrets, landing gear) and those details later printed in a resin printer for accuracy.
There is some work in the lateral clamps as I have added a 4mm magnet slot and modified the width to fit new rhinos/big grimdark containers.

* 2024-02-10 Update: Add missing lower rear reactor piece and update renders

I have explicitly asked STROGANOFF for modifying and sharing this asset. Be respectful with your fellow artists :)

A re-design of the original miniature produced by Games Workshop for their 6mm scale table top wargame, Epic 40,000 (and precessors/successors). They have since abandoned all support for Epic, so I modeled this in Autodesk Inventor for any avid wargamers who don't want to use proxies or pay through the nose for OOP official models off Ebay.

I haven't tried printing this model in an FDM printer so I can't recommend settings or methods of optimization.

Epic has been re-released as a titans-only game called Adeptus Titanicus. It is nominally 8mm scale instead of 6mm, so I suggest that anyone wanting to print this for AT scenery or to play 8mm Epic should upscale it by 125%.
